# === GitHub Linguist language-bar overrides ===
#
# This repo is a set of AI agent / skill / rule *definitions* authored in
# Markdown, with shell used only as glue (hooks, the sync script, tests).
#
# Linguist excludes `prose` (Markdown) and `data` (JSON) from the language bar
# by default, so the ~600 KB of Markdown that *is* the product was dropped and
# the ~65 KB of glue shell became the only "detectable" language -> a misleading
# "Shell 100%". These overrides make the bar reflect the repo's real content:
# Markdown-defined AI orchestration.

# Count the Markdown that defines the orchestration (prose is excluded by default).
*.md    linguist-detectable=true

# Cursor rule files are Markdown with frontmatter: classify and count them.
*.mdc   linguist-language=Markdown linguist-detectable=true

# Shell is glue, not the product -> drop it from the language bar.
# (detectable=false, not vendored: hooks are first-party and still show in diffs.)
*.sh    linguist-detectable=false

# The plugin tree is generated from .claude/ by scripts/sync-plugin.sh.
# Mark it generated so the mirror neither inflates stats nor clutters diffs.
# (Listed last so it wins over the broad rules above for files under it.)
plugins/agent-team/**   linguist-generated=true
